{
  "id": "019d3179-7fa6-77f2-b4ce-c31ca693a0a5",
  "content": "## GC Observability and Telemetry (Issue #23, PR #46)\n\nInstrumented the GC worker with structured tracing and enriched search/status APIs with tier metadata.\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- **`corvia.gc.cycle` span**: Uses `#[tracing::instrument]` with all metric fields (entries_scanned, transitions_*, promotions_*, rebuild_triggered/duration_ms, forgotten_access_attempts, cycle_duration_ms). Fields recorded via `Span::current().record()` at cycle end.\n- **Transition log**: Each tier transition emits structured `info!(\"tier_transition\")` with full score breakdown (d/a/g/c weighted components) + reason enum (\"score_decay\" | \"inactivity\" | \"budget_policy\"). Components are weighted values that sum to total (pre-supersession penalty).\n- **ScoreBreakdown API**: `compute_retention_score_breakdown()` returns individual weighted components. `compute_retention_score()` now delegates to it (DRY).\n- **ForgottenAccessCounter**: Shared `AtomicU64` (Relaxed ordering) incremented by MCP history/graph handlers when accessing Forgotten entries. GC cycle takes+resets per span. Passed as `Option<Arc<>>` to `spawn_gc_worker`, `Option<&>` to `run_gc_cycle`.\n- **SearchResult.tier**: Non-optional `Tier` field (not `Option<Tier>`) since every real store always populates it. Display format (lowercase \"hot\"/\"warm\"/\"cold\"/\"forgotten\") used in DTOs, not Debug.\n- **TierDistribution in system_status**: Uses lightweight `count_tiers_by_scope()` with partial deserialization (`TierOnly` struct) to avoid loading full entries+embeddings. Exposed in both REST (via Serialize) and MCP (manual JSON).\n- **History handler optimization**: Checks Forgotten tier from the returned chain entries instead of an extra `store.get()` call.\n\n### Review Findings Applied\n- tier_distribution must be explicitly included in MCP system_status JSON (not auto-serialized)\n- scope_id removed from GC cycle span (multi-scope cycles have no single scope)\n- Display instead of Debug for Tier in API responses (consistency with serde)\n- compute_retention_score delegates to _breakdown (eliminates DRY violation)",
  "source_version": "mcp",
